==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from: '''1611,''' [[w:King James Version of the Bible|King James Version of the Bible]], [[w:Epistle to the Galatians|Epistle to the Galatians]], [[s:Bible (King James)/Galatians#Chapter 6|6:7]]
:* Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|en-au-as you sow, so shall you reap.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb}}

# {{lb|en|figurative}} The personal [[consequences]] of one's actions are in [[proportion]] to the good or bad [[intentions]] towards others.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|reap what one sows|you reap what you sow}}

